Weather analysis

# download data manually from https://www.dmi.dk/friedata/observationer/
# or
# download weather data through API --> see below

parameters_of_interest <- readLines("data/weather/README.md", n = 30)[21:30]

# get your personal api-key from a place you saved it
apikey <- readLines("data/weather/README.md", n = 4)[4]

# define function that access data on the DMI Open Data website
fetch_weather_param <- function(param, nobs=10^4){
  # nobs must be an integer between 1 and 300,000
  if(nobs>3*10^5) stop("number of requested observations cannot be larger than 300,000")
  # glue nobs, parameter of interest, and api-key into url 
  url <- str_glue("https://dmigw.govcloud.dk/v2/metObs/collections/observation/items?limit={nobs}&datetime=2013-01-01T00:00:00Z/2021-12-31T23:59:59Z&stationId=06074&parameterId={param}&api-key={apikey}")
  # download json data from url
  rjson::fromJSON(file = url)
}

# define function that transform JSON format to data.frame
json_to_df <- function(json){
  ldf <- lapply(1:length(json$features),
         function(i) dplyr::bind_cols( json$features[[i]]$properties ) )
  df <- rbindlist(ldf)
  df %>% pivot_wider(id_cols = c("stationId","observed"),
                     names_from="parameterId", values_from="value")
}


# apply functions with your favorite parameters
# here: wind, rain and temp
ldf <- lapply(parameters_of_interest[c(1,4,8)],
              function(param){
                param_json <- fetch_weather_param(param = param, nobs = 10^5)
                param_df <- json_to_df(param_json)
                })
# merge data
dt_weather <- Reduce("merge", ldf) %>% as.data.table()
# make data-observations to a data format
dt_weather[, observed := as_datetime(observed)]

# add datatime variables
dt_weather[, `:=`(year=year(observed),
         month=month(observed),
         day=day(observed),
         weekday=wday(observed, week_start = 1),
         weekday_label=wday(observed, week_start = 1, label = TRUE),
         hour=hour(observed))]

# check that we have the preferred data range (from 2013 to 2022; both inclusive)
dt_weather[, range(observed)]

join weather data with playing data

dt_plays_day <- dt[grepl("(Tilst|Grimh|Vestereng|Risskov)", courseId) &
     !(year==2021 & month==11) & hour>=8 & hour<=20, .(n_play=.N),
   by=.(year, month, weekday)]
# summary(dt_plays_day_weather)


join.by.cols <- intersect(colnames(dt_plays_day), colnames(dt_weather_day))

dt_plays_day_weather <- dt_plays_day %>%
  full_join(dt_weather_day, by = join.by.cols) %>%
  mutate(n_play=ifelse(is.na(n_play),0, n_play)) %>%
  arrange(year, month, day)

plot weather data

p_precip <- dt_plays_day_weather %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = precip, y=n_play)) +
  # geom_point() +
  geom_hex(show.legend = F) +
  scale_fill_viridis_c(direction = -1) +
  scale_y_log10(name = "Daily number of rounds",
                labels = function(x) format(x, big.mark = ",")) +
  labs(x = "Precip (mm)") +
  theme_bw()

p_wind <- dt_plays_day_weather %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = wind, y=n_play)) +
  # geom_point() +
  geom_hex(show.legend = F) +
  scale_fill_viridis_c(direction = -1) +
  scale_y_log10() +
  labs(x = "Wind (m/s)") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank())

p_temp <- dt_plays_day_weather %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = temp, y=n_play)) +
  # geom_point() +
  geom_hex(show.legend = F) +
  scale_fill_viridis_c(direction = -1) +
  scale_y_log10() +
  labs(x = "Temp (*C)") +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.title.y = element_blank(), axis.text.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank())

p_precip + p_wind + p_temp +
  plot_layout(nrow = 1) +

p_weather <- dt_weather_day[year==2021] %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c("precip", "wind", "temp"), names_to="param") %>%
  filter(param!="precip" | (param=="precip" & value>0 & value <100)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = value, fill = param)) +
  geom_density(alpha=0.5, show.legend = F) +
  facet_wrap(param~., scales="free")

p_weather_play <- dt_plays_day_weather[year==2021][, precip.log:=log10(precip)] %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c("precip", "wind", "temp"), names_to="param") %>%
  filter(param!="precip" | (param=="precip" & value>0 & value <100)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(value, n_play)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .2) +
  # geom_density2d() +
  # geom_hex(color="black") +
  scale_fill_viridis_c(direction = -1) +
  facet_grid(year~param, scales="free")

p_weather + p_weather_play + plot_layout(ncol=1)

Conclusions:

  • It looks like disc golfers doesnt care about the rain.
  • There may be a positive correlation between temp and play.
  • People do not play in winds above 7.5 m/s.

Limitations: There a lot of confounders when looking into whether data without correcting for seasonal changes in weather. E.g. lower temperatures in winter and shorter days in winter. Players have less time during daylight to play.
